Databases - Used for persistent data
	• A collection of information/data
	• Has an interface (language to manipulate the data)

SQL (relational) vs. NoSQL (non-relational)

SQL...
• Been around the longest
• Follows a set pattern
• Uses tables (tabular)
• Very rigid
• Flat

NoSQL...
• Looks like JavaScript
• Not flat
• Flexible structure
• What will be used in this course
• Not better or worse than SQL